  • Sage Originals

    Cases commissioned, developed, and published by Sage. Including teaching notes, discussion questions, and learning objectives.

    • All Sage Originals
      All Sage Originals
      Peer-reviewed cases from authors around the world. All come with discussion questions, learning outcomes, and teaching notes.
    • Express
      Express
      Short, news-driven SAGE Original cases that are published quarterly to help bring current events into the classroom.
    • Accounting
      Accounting
      Accelerate and elevate your decision-making and quantitative skills with this series of cases featuring contemporary accounting dilemmas.
    • Ancient Leadership
      Ancient Leadership
      Explore narratives from ancient history and mythology. Themes include becoming a leader, emotional intelligence, and transitions of power.
    • Coaching & Mentoring
      Coaching & Mentoring
      Think beyond your own advancement and learn how you can help others learn and grow.
    • Customer Experience
      Customer Experience
      Discover best practices for measuring and improving customer experience.
    • Digital Entertainment
      Digital Entertainment
      From video games to virtual ballet performances, explore the business & management of digital entertainment.
    • Economic History
      Economic History
      Learn how markets function in different settings, with well-researched and explained historical examples.
    • Events Management
      Events Management
      How can people gather safely? Discover common issues and best practices.
    • Family Business
      Family Business
      This series highlights the challenges faced by family businesses across different cultural contexts.
    • Food Marketing
      Food Marketing
      Consider perspectives of producers, retailers, and customers in cases that discuss current events in the world of food and beverages.
    • Global Marketing
      Global Marketing
      Brainstorm how to address the challenges of introducing or expanding a business in a new cultural context.
    • Healthcare Management
      Healthcare Management
      Discover ethical and financial dilemmas encountered by healthcare providers and related firms. Compare strategies to optimize health.
    • Humanities and Arts in Business
      Humanities and Arts in Business
      Creative business pedagogy that is inspired by and utilizes material from classic and contemporary humanities and arts.
    • Immigrant Entrepreneurs
      Immigrant Entrepreneurs
      Discover challenges faced and strategies used by entrepreneurs who have migrated from one country to another.
    • International Strategy
      International Strategy
      This series focuses on the intersection of market strategy and global business and the varied challenges therein.
    • Logistics
      Logistics
      Explore the process of coordinating and moving resources — people or products — from one location to its desired destination.
    • Music Marketing
      Music Marketing
      Explore economic, legal, and artistic challenges faced by both musicians and companies that use music to reach customers.
    • Social Impact
      Social Impact
      This series spotlights a broad spectrum of cases on all topics related to social impact, social business, and social entrepreneurship.
    • Sustainability
      Sustainability
      Analyze strategies to combat climate change and preserve natural resources across industries and world regions.
    • Valuation
      Valuation
      Explores valuation skills from the quantitative skills of inputting data into models and obtaining the valuation to soft skills needed to commun...
    • Venture Capital
      Venture Capital
      Explore common challenges related to start-ups, with a particular focus on funding.
    • Women & Leadership
      Women & Leadership
      Focusing on the varying roles of women in international business, this series provides role models and lessons for students and future leaders.
